LAION-Comp sits clearly between Jigsaw3D (4.5, reject) and the borderline-accept cluster (6.0). It has real strengths that exceed Jigsaw3D: a much larger dataset contribution, testing across four backbones, some external-benchmark validation (T2I-CompBench, COCO-Stuff, VG), and a complete system (dataset + model + benchmark + editing). However, it falls short of the 6.0 borderline accept papers because:

